---
By: James Allen
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 418
    Verse: 2
Tags:
  - Selfishness
---
Personality, separateness, selfishness are one and the same, and are
the antithesis of wisdom and divinity. By the unqualified surrender of
personality, separateness and selfishness cease, and man enters into the
possession of his divine heritage.
